 \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 481, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"herdressage\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 550}, {\"ngram\": \"a score\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 598}, {\"ngram\": \"the first phase\", \"from\": 612, \"to\": 627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was amazing and London is just my horse of a lifetime,\\\" said an emotional Laura.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just my horse\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"a lifetime\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 691}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's just incredible.\", \"from\": 719, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not really believe we have just done that, to be honest.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just relieved that it's over and I have not let anyone down.\\\"\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura said that the crowds were \\\"unbelievable\\\" and that it was a \\\"buzz from start to finish\\\".\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the crowds\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"buzz\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"start\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"finish\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 34-year-old rider, who won team gold on London 52 at the Tokyo Olympics has produced this gelding since he was a young horse.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 34-year-old rider\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"team gold\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1045}, {\"ngram\": \"this gelding\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"a young horse\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think for me, knowing what he was like as a young horse and knowing how much he's had to trust me and believe in me - he's not a natural cross-country horse and then he goes around a course like that on railway tracks, so it just shows what a partnership you can build up and you can make them believe in you,\\\" she explained.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a young horse\", \"from\": 1146, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"a natural cross-country horse\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"a course\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"railway tracks\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"what a partnership\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have full faith in him now, which means I can go and enjoy myself out there.\\\"\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"full faith\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura said that the optimum tight is \\\"tight\\\" but that London 52 losing a front shoe early on course did not help her to finish inside the time.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a front shoe\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are a couple of places where you can really let them gallop, but there are an awful lot of twists and turns and after he lost a shoe, he was slipping all over the place.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a couple\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1676}, {\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1686}, {\"ngram\": \"an awful lot\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"twists\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"turns\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1771}, {\"ngram\": \"a shoe\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"the place\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That meant I had to be quite careful on those turns and really kill the speed to get around the trees without doing anything stupid like slipping over.\\\"\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those turns\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"the speed\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"the trees\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking of London's lost shoe, Laura stated: \\\"Fingers crossed the team will get him sorted tonight and yes, it's not not ideal, but it just shows what a good horse he is.\\\"\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2000, \"end\": 2006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997505333651, \"rank\": 1.4766591856174517e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fingers\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"what a good horse\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the Pierre Le Goupil-designed Olympic cross-country track, Laura said it had provoked a lot of \\\"head scratching\\\".\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2224, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Pierre Le Goupil-designed Olympic cross-country track\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2222}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To be honest, up until this morning I was planning to jump the right hand corner coming out of the second water [at fence 10 - The Vauban Citadel], but I watched a few jump it and it looked like the striding to the left corner was just a bit easier and more obvious for the horses so I changed my mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 2280, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this morning\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2316}, {\"ngram\": \"the right hand corner\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2361}, {\"ngram\": \"the second water\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"fence\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"The Vauban Citadel\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2426}, {\"ngram\": \"the striding\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2488}, {\"ngram\": \"the left corner\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"the horses\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2561}, {\"ngram\": \"my mind\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura also said her plan as always to go off the left-hand side drop at the influential fence 16abcd, The Viewpoint over the Grand Canal.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2723, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2586, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her plan\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the left-hand side drop\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2654}, {\"ngram\": \"the influential fence\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2679}, {\"ngram\": \"The Viewpoint\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2701}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Canal\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was always very much wanting to jump left off the drop - I just felt like the ditch was a bit of a nothing ditch and there were too many unknown circumstances there for how horses would read it and jump it with only two strides to the triple brush out.\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the drop\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2782}, {\"ngram\": \"the ditch\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"a bit\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"a nothing ditch\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2840}, {\"ngram\": \"too many unknown circumstances\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"only two strides\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2955}, {\"ngram\": \"the triple brush\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I just thought that was an unnecessary risk, so for me that was always plan A and stuck to it and it rode really nicely.\\\"\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an unnecessary risk\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura's phenomenal two-phase score, paired with British pathfinderTom McEwen's clear round inside the timewith JL Dublin means that after the second rotation of team riders, the British team has a commanding lead over the rest of the field with France in second and Japan in third.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3104, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9986764070127014, \"rank\": 0.0013253457836207559, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}, {\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \